    "headline": "Match Group invests $100 million in Grindr rival Sniffies with buyout option",
    "summary": "Match Group is investing $100 million in Sniffies, a dating platform ‌targeted at non-heterosexual men, in a ‌deal giving the Tinder parent a significant minority position ​and the option of buying out the remaining equity in the future. Match has been attempting a turnaround in recent times, reworking ‌core features across ⁠its lineup to reduce negative experiences and focus on user experience ⁠as younger users grow more selective with dating apps. Sniffies has grown to an ​estimated 3 ​million monthly active ​users globally, according to ‌Match's statement.",
